03/06/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police detained a man Tuesday (June 2nd) suspected of killing eight relatives in the southern city of Adana.
The dead include his parents, a brother and two young nephews, according to Governor Ilhan Atis.
The suspect, 38-year-old Murat Yuksel, was caught while writing a suicide note, and with a gun believed to be the murder weapon.
He has confessed to the killings, Atis said, though the motive is unclear.
(CNNTurk, NTV, Hurriyet, Zaman, Anadolu news agency, Dogan news agency, Reuters, AFP, CNN - 02/06/09)
